boone.spike

Class SpikeSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • boone.PatternSet
      • boone.spike.SpikeSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Storable, java.lang.Cloneable

    public class SpikeSet
extends PatternSet
    A spike set links lists of doubles to specific neurons. Each value in a list represents a point in the simulation time. There are three different types of lists in a spike set:

    • Inputs: Each value in the list defines a point in the simulation time, at which the linked input neuron will emit a spike.
    • Targets: Each value in the list defines a point in the simulation time, at which the linked output neuron is expected to emit a spike. The values in this list do not control the output of the specified neuron. Its intended use is to train a SpikingNeuralNet.
    • Outputs: Each value in the list represents a point in the simulation time, at which the linked output neuron emitted a spike.

    Use SpikingNeuralNet.setInput(SpikeSet) to set the network input to the input data of a given spike set. Use SpikingNeuron.record(SpikeSet, double, double) or SpikingNeuron.recordStart(SpikeSet) to record the output of a specific SpikingNeuron into a given spike set .
